[[File:Landscape at Vogelenzang.jpg|thumb|right|Landscape at [[Vogelenzang]], 1834, [[Teylers First Painting Gallery]]]] '''Gerrit Jan Michaëlis''' (1775, [[Amsterdam]] &ndash; 1857, [[Haarlem]]), was an 18th-century painter from the Northern Netherlands.
==Biography== He was the son of the sculptor H.C. Michaëlis who studied at the ''Koninklijke Academie voor Beeldende Kunsten'' (Amsterdam Royal Academy of Art) and became a member of the Amsterdam drawing society called "''Tekengenootschap Zonder Wet of Spreuk''".<ref name=RKD>[https://rkd.nl/en/explore/artists/55844 Gerrit Jan Michaëlis] in the [[RKD]]</ref> He was the pupil of [[George Nikolaus Ritter]] and [[Jurriaan Andriessen (artist)|Jurriaan Andriessen]], and won a prize at the Amsterdam drawing academy [[Felix Meritis]] in 1805.<ref name=RKD/><ref name=Willig>[http://www.historici.nl/retroboeken/vaderlandsche_schilderkunst/#source=III&page=204 History of art] by [[Adriaan van der Willigen]] and [[Roeland van Eynden]]</ref> He continued to send in examples of his art which met with success in Amsterdam competitions in the years 1808, 1810, 1813, 1814, 1816, and 1818.<ref name=Willig/>
He moved to Haarlem to succeed [[Wybrand Hendriks]] as the curator and live-in kastelein of the art collection at the [[Teylers Museum]] during the years 1819-1854.<ref name=RKD/> He is known for his landscapes and was also the director of the Haarlem Stadstekenacademie.<ref name=RKD/> {{commons category|Gerrit Jan Michaëlis}}
==References== {{reflist}}
==External links== * [http://www.artnet.com/artists/gerrit-jan-michaelis/past-auction-results Gerrit Jan Michaëlis] on [[Artnet]] * [http://www.rijksmuseum.nl/collectie/RP-T-2010-62/portret-g-j-micha%c3%ablis His sketched portrait] on the [[Rijksmuseum]] website by [[Jacob Ernst Marcus]]
{{Authority control}}
