{{About|a place devoted to the imagination|the [[Nightwish]] album|Imaginaerum|other uses of the word|Imaginarium (disambiguation)}}
An '''imaginarium''' refers to a place devoted to the [[imagination]]. There are various types of imaginaria, centers largely devoted to stimulating and cultivating the imagination, towards scientific, artistic, commercial, recreational, or spiritual ends.{{citation needed|date=December 2014}}
==Existing imaginariums== * The '''Imaginarium Discovery Center''' is a children's science discovery center within the [[Anchorage Museum]] in [[Anchorage, Alaska|Anchorage]] in the [[U.S. state]] of [[Alaska]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Imaginarium Discovery Center|url=https://www.anchoragemuseum.org/exhibits-events/permanent-exhibits/imaginarium-discovery-center/|publisher=Anchorage Museum|accessdate=20 November 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129053632/https://www.anchoragemuseum.org/exhibits-events/permanent-exhibits/imaginarium-discovery-center/|archivedate=29 November 2014|df=}}</ref> * The '''Imaginarium of South Texas''' is a children's museum and informal science center at [[Mall del Norte]] in [[Laredo, Texas|Laredo]], [[Texas]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.istx.org/#!imagine-award/cdcs|title=2013 Imagine Award Winners|publisher=istx.org|accessdate=October 13, 2015}}</ref> * The '''Imaginarium Science Center''' is a science museum and aquarium in [[Fort Myers, Florida]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Official site|url=http://www.imaginariumfortmyers.com/|publisher=Imaginarium Science Center|accessdate=20 November 2014}}</ref> It features science exhibits, a 3-D theatre, dinosaurs, aquarium displays, a touch tank with stingrays and more. * The '''Imaginarium Science Centre''' of [[Devonport, Tasmania]] is a hands-on science museum that is part of Pandemonium: Discovery and Adventure Centre.<ref>{{cite web|title=Imaginarium Science Centre|url=http://www.pandemoniumtas.com.au/imaginarium/|publisher=Pandemonium: Discovery and Adventure Centre|accessdate=20 November 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141130002806/http://www.pandemoniumtas.com.au/imaginarium/|archivedate=30 November 2014|df=}}</ref>
==Imaginaria in popular culture== In ''[[The Imaginarium of Doctor Parnassus]]'', the immortal mystic Doctor Parnassus runs a nomadic theater troupe who lure people through a mirror that shows them a world of their deepest subconscious desires, where their souls are put to the test.
