[[Category:Hermitage Museum]]

The '''North West Sound Archive''' was founded in [[Manchester]] in 1979. It was relocated to [[Clitheroe]] in 1982, where it occupied the third floor of the [[Clitheroe Castle Museum]].<ref name="guidebook" /> {{coord| 53.8702|-2.3931|display=title,inline}} 
It was the largest archive of sound recordings in the UK outside London, holding over 140,000 items.<ref name="LT_22Dec14" /> The archive was closed in 2015 due to financial circumstances.<ref name="LT_22Dec14" /> The archive material was relocated to the [[Manchester Central Library]], [[Liverpool Central Library]], and the [[Lancashire Archives]], depending on the location that the material related to.<ref name="nwsound" />

